<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Starting With DIS- — Scrabble Prefix Scoring Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The DIS- prefix reverses or negates the root word's meaning and is one of the most prolific prefixes in Scrabble. With 800+ valid words, DIS- creates countless extension opportunities — turning AGREE into DISAGREE, PLACE into DISPLACE, and opening bingo paths from nearly any board position.</p>

<p>The D tile alone is worth 2 points, giving DIS- a slight scoring edge over prefixes built entirely from 1-point tiles.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why DIS- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">D(2)+I(1)+S(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">800+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid DIS- words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>DIS- is the single most productive prefix in Scrabble by raw word count. Because it attaches to verbs, nouns, and adjectives alike, you can almost always find an extension if you hold D-I-S on your rack.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring DIS- Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
