<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Prepend to board words:</span> If PLACE, OWN, or ARM appear on the board, prepending DIS creates a valid word instantly. This is one of the safest prefix extensions in the game.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack flexibility:</span> D, I, and S are all common draws — you'll frequently have the DIS- setup without specifically fishing for it. When you notice it on your rack, scan the board for extension targets.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo factory:</span> DIS- plus any 4-letter root creates a 7-letter bingo. DISBAND, DISCARD, DISRUPT, DISTORT — keep DIS together and hunt for short roots on the board.</p>
  </div>
</div>

